        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-01-05 12:35:24.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\n> Michael, there should be option to trigger jenkins job when there is a new review. And the job can vote accordingly to success or failure.\n\nRight, and I can help set this up if you want.",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
      {
        "id": "30b35086819d9f79bb09a5512a42cff2bcfa8b6c",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1077,
          "name": "Michael O'Brien",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "frank.obrien@amdocs.com",
          "username": "michaelobrien"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-01-05 13:06:39.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nCorrect, a CI/CD system for OOM is in the works - in discussions moving our POC to the LF's jenkins servers",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
      {
        "id": "4882ff65d23b35b3a8b60bfaa4cb57d4d3541a1c",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1077,
          "name": "Michael O'Brien",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "frank.obrien@amdocs.com",
          "username": "michaelobrien"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-01-05 13:11:11.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nI agree - usually java based projects trigger the \"ONAP JobBuilder\" - which sends back a success +1 and an email - since we are infrastructure we will need to propose a new version of this jobBuilder - just for CD not CI - I'll raise a jira and cc the linux helpdesk",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
      {
        "id": "f146e5b36b1cff036ae5c66625f50b76eec2915b",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1077,
          "name": "Michael O'Brien",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "frank.obrien@amdocs.com",
          "username": "michaelobrien"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-01-05 13:13:43.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nWhen JIRA is fixed - I add 2 subtasks off OOM-500 - one for the trigger on OOM changes (CD of OOM itself), and one for the trigger to run CD on any ONAP docker change (normal CD)",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
      {
        "id": "a0a089ca9da8756e2a5cea4208ff8d1bfeedbfe1",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 137,
          "name": "Alexis de Talhouet",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "adetalhouet89@gmail.com",
          "username": "adetalhouet"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-01-05 13:35:35.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\n> I agree - usually java based projects trigger the \"ONAP JobBuilder\" - which sends back a success +1 and an email - since we are infrastructure we will need to propose a new version of this jobBuilder - just for CD not CI - I'll raise a jira and cc the linux helpdesk\n\nWell actually we do want CI as well. When someone push a patch, we can just validate it's sementic are correct, with a helm install --dry-run. Then if that pass, we can trigger CD that will test and install. So I think we need both, so we can fail fast if sementic is not respected.\nRegarding trigger this on patch committed, this is very straightforward to do (at least I know very well how to do it). Maybe we should first flush out the detail of what the CI/CD should look like, that we might already thanks to the work you've done. Then create a ticket in OOM tracking this, and I can take care of the wiring in LF Jenkins, and create the jobs accordingly.",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
      {
        "id": "737560d04120c6fa6c3d25cb1597d4f9fc39ed57",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1077,
          "name": "Michael O'Brien",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "frank.obrien@amdocs.com",
          "username": "michaelobrien"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-01-05 14:01:24.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nSounds good - we always wanted full CI/CD on any code, docker or infrastructure change - there are several jiras - we could key off OOM-500, OOM-150 or INT-300 or INT-120",
        "patchset_number": 6
